    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-09-15T19:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-09-15T19:30:00-05:00" n="52"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                <head>52. Handwritten Note Prepared by the Ambassador to Israel (<persName
                        corresp="#p_LSW_1">Lewis</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d52fn1">Source: Department of State, <gloss target="#t_US_1"
                            >U.S.</gloss> Embassy Tel Aviv, Principal Officer Program Files, Lot
                        85F104, Personal for Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_LSW_1"
                            >Lewis</persName>—Sensitive Notes 1978. No classification marking. See
                            <ref target="#d28fn72">footnote 72, Document 28</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Camp David</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1978-09-15T20:30:00-04:00">September 15, 1978, 8:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_LSW_1"
                            >Lewis</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BA_2">Barak</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_DS_1">Dinitz</persName>
                    </hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> went over Egyptian
                        suggestions<note n="2" xml:id="d52fn2">See <ref target="#d28fn71">footnote
                            71, Document 28</ref>.</note>—<persName corresp="#p_BA_2"
                        >Barak</persName> accepted some, rejected others. Will call back tomorrow on
                    some.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BA_2">Barak</persName>:</hi> p.6—OK. p.7—OK. With
                    regard to <gloss target="#t_para_1">para</gloss> A–1–(c)<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d52fn3">Reference is to Paragraph 1(c), of Section A of the
                        “Framework for Peace in the Middle East”, which covers the process whereby
                        the final status of the West Bank and Gaza, and the territories’ relations
                        with its neighbors, would be determined. For the complete text of the
                        Framework agreement as drafted and introduced by the <gloss target="#t_US_1"
                            >U.S.</gloss> delegation on September 9, see <ref target="#d40">Document
                            40</ref>. For the complete text of the Framework as signed by <persName
                            corresp="#p_CJE_2">Carter</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BM_2"
                            >Begin</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName> at
                        the White House, see <ref target="#d57">Document 57</ref>.</note> (p. 7–8)
                    several problems:</p>
                <p>1) last sentence (“own form of govt”)—I discussed with <gloss target="#t_MB_1"
                        >MB</gloss>. He agrees to (change).</p>
                <p>2) re (d)—The peace treaty will be submitted for approval to the elected
                    representatives of the parties.”</p>
                <p>(or <hi rend="italic">maybe</hi>—“submitted to the vote of the elected reps of
                    the parties.”)</p>
                <p>3) (c)—<persName corresp="#p_BA_2">Barak</persName> has new language:</p>
                <p>(<hi rend="italic">gave copy</hi>)</p>
                <p>Purpose of word “also”: means final solution must <hi rend="italic">also</hi>
                    cover poss. claim of sovereign[ty] by both Jordan, Israel, etc.</p>
                <p>i.e. to <persName corresp="#p_BA_2">Barak</persName>—<hi rend="italic">also</hi>
                    means “other claims”.</p>
                <p>To Egyptions—<hi rend="italic">also</hi> could mean + self-determination</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_CV_1">CV</gloss>—I think it’s a real step. Re the <hi
                        rend="italic">old</hi> text of (c), other problems:</p>
                <p>Reads whole new “c” per <persName corresp="#p_BA_2">Barak</persName>.</p>
                <p>9:20—<persName corresp="#p_WE_1">Weizman</persName>/<persName corresp="#p_TA_1"
                        >Tamir</persName> join us.</p>
                <p>He had just dropped in on <persName corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName>—½
                    hour.</p>
                <p>Free access tomorrow.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
